jif.summary: Recent activities in the jif repository include multiple push events with updates such as initial parts of bfexec, refactoring, addition of a makefile, implementation of a function to convert bf source code into intermediate representation, and creation of a LICENSE file, all contributing to the ongoing development and refinement of the project.

cmkr.summary: The cmkr repository has seen a recent push event that involved refactoring by inlining a single-use function, contributing to code optimization and simplification, while the build-cpp/cmkr repository had a pull request event focused on adding a check for valid hex hashes, addressing issue #152.

build-cpp/cmkr.summary: A significant pull request was made to the build-cpp/cmkr repository, introducing a check to ensure that hashes are valid hexadecimal, effectively resolving issue #152 and enhancing the repository's functionality and reliability.
